The paper deals with the analysis of auction mechanisms, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT). It specifically focuses on position auctions for keyword advertisements, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of computational methods to analyze the auctions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses economic quantities such as social welfare and revenue, indicating that it may also be relevant to the subfield of computational economics (cs.EC).
